CHANGELOG
=========

This file follows Keep a Changelog (https://keepachangelog.com/) and
SemVer with the relaxation declared in docs/PLAN.md §12 decision 12:
v0.x is unstable; v1.0.0 freezes the public API.

## Unreleased — 2026-05-07 (SDK link-validation pass)

First end-to-end build of the cgo backend against an installed SAP
NetWeaver RFC SDK (7.50 PL18, Linux x86_64, build 637). The previous
v1.0.0 surface was specified and unit-tested without the SDK in
hand. This pass linked `internal/sdkbackend` against the real
`libsapnwrfc.so` for the first time.

### Fixed (cgo backend regressions surfaced by the link step)

- internal/sdkbackend: helpers `goMallocU` / `goFreeU` /
  `goStrlenU` / `goSetParamActive` were defined as `static`
  functions inside the cgo preamble of `cgo_directives.go`, which
  made them invisible to the cgo preambles of sibling files (each
  Go file with `import "C"` carries its own preamble). Extracted
  to `internal/sdkbackend/helpers.{c,h}` so they have package-wide
  linkage. Each cgo `.go` file now does `#include "helpers.h"`.
  AGENTS.md §Engineering Rules: explicit malloc/free pairing kept
  grep-able in one file.
- internal/sdkbackend/helpers.c: `goFreeU` now calls the standard
  `free()`. The SDK's `<sapucrfc.h>` defines `mallocU` as a macro
  that expands to `mallocU16(len)` → `(SAP_UTF16*) malloc(len *
  sizeof(SAP_UTF16))`. There is **no** matching `freeU` macro in
  the public header set; the previous binding referenced one. The
  legacy `gorfc/gorfc.go` had this right (see its 224-227 comment
  block). Documented in `docs/SDK_FUNCTIONS_MAP.md`.
- internal/sdkbackend/conn.go: `attr.type_` → `attr._type`. cgo
  prefixes (not suffixes) Go-keyword field names with `_`, so the
  C field `type` becomes `_type` on the Go side. The bug was a
  typo against cgo's renaming rule; sibling code in
  `internal/sdkbackend/{fill,wrap}.go` already used `pd._type`
  correctly.
- internal/sdkbackend/fill.go: `fillFunctionParameter` was passing
  a `C.RFC_FUNCTION_HANDLE` directly to `fillVariable`, whose
  signature expects `unsafe.Pointer`. cgo represents `void*`
  typedefs as opaque pointer types that don't implicitly convert
  to `unsafe.Pointer`; added the explicit `unsafe.Pointer(fh)`
  conversion (matching `wrap.go:46`).

### Test hardening (separate SDK-free from SAP-backed)

- gorfc/gorfc_test.go: every integration test now calls
  `gorfcTestEnvOrSkip(t)` at entry. The helper existed but was
  not invoked, so without `GORFC_TEST_USER` set the tests would
  panic on a nil `*Connection`. Per AGENTS.md §Engineering Rules:
  "Tests must separate SDK-free unit tests from SAP-backed
  integration tests."
- nwrfc/conn_nosdk_test.go (new) + nwrfc/conn_test.go: moved
  `TestOpen_NoSDK_SurfacesAsSDKUnavailable` behind a
  `//go:build !cgo || nwrfc_nosdk` tag. The test asserts that
  the no-SDK stub backend surfaces `*SDKUnavailableError`, which
  is the wrong assertion when the cgo+SDK backend is actually
  wired in.

### Documentation (SDK reality)

- docs/SDK_FUNCTIONS_MAP.md: flipped 🟡 → ✅ for symbols whose
  existence is now confirmed by `nm -D libsapnwrfc.so` against
  PL18: `RfcCancel`, `RfcSetParameterActive`, `RfcSetIniPath`,
  `RfcReloadIniFile`, `RfcLoadCryptoLibrary`,
  `RfcLanguageIsoToSap` / `RfcLanguageSapToIso`,
  `RfcIsConnectionHandleValid`, `RfcGetTypeLength`,
  `RfcAddFunctionDesc` / `RfcRemoveFunctionDesc`, the throughput
  family (7.53+), the tRFC family, the bgRFC family, the server
  install handlers (`RfcInstallTransactionHandlers`,
  `RfcInstallBgRfcHandlers`,
  `RfcInstall{Generic,}ServerFunction`), and `RfcRegisterServer`
  / `RfcShutdownServer` / `RfcListenAndDispatch`.
- docs/SDK_FUNCTIONS_MAP.md "Phantom symbols" section: two
  symbols previously documented in PLAN.md drafts do **not**
  exist in PL18 (`nm -D` confirmed):
  - `RfcStartOrResumeServer` — the real SDK symbol is
    `RfcStartServer` (sapnwrfc.h:1441). Server accept loops use
    `RfcListenAndDispatch`.
  - `RfcSetQueueName` — qRFC routing in NW RFC SDK 7.50 is done
    by passing the queue list to `RfcCreateUnit`, not via a
    separate setter.
  Per AGENTS.md non-negotiables ("Do not introduce silent
  fallback behavior"), these are now flagged 🔴 in the map.
- nwrfc/transactional.go: comment in `Transaction.Submit`
  updated to reflect the qRFC reality (queue routing via
  `RfcCreateUnit`, not `RfcSetQueueName`).

### Pending — Categoria B (live SAP system)

The following gates remain blocked on a reachable SAP test system
with classic RFC enabled:

- STFC_CONNECTION + STFC_STRUCTURE round-trip
- `RfcCancel` actual cancel-mid-call timing
- tRFC `Submit` / `Confirm` against `SM58`
- bgRFC `Unit` lifecycle visible in `SBGRFCMON`
- `RfcInstallTransactionHandlers` / `RfcInstallBgRfcHandlers`
  trampoline (T3.4 cgo glue)
- qRFC reimplementation over `RfcCreateUnit`

Browser-only access (Fiori / S/4HANA Cloud Public) is **not**
sufficient for these — classic RFC needs the dispatcher port
(`32<sysnr>`) reachable, which Cloud Public Edition does not
expose. The SDK is in hand; the system is the gate.

## v1.0.0 — 2026-05-07 (Tier 4: Go-native differentiation, GA)

### Added — Tier 4

- nwrfcmock package (T4.1): pure-Go [backend.Backend]
  implementation. HandleFunc / SetDescriptor / SetVersion /
  SetCapabilities + CallCount / OpenCount / CloseCount
  counters. Routes nwrfc.Call through user-registered handlers
  for hermetic unit tests; no cgo, no SAP system needed.
- cmd/nwrfc-gen (T4.2): codegen tool that produces typed Go
  client packages from a SAP function descriptor. Live mode
  connects to a SAP system; offline mode reads a JSON
  descriptor (suitable for vendoring schemas in source).
  Generated code is gofmt'd, has no runtime overhead beyond
  the marshal layer the core library already pays.
- nwrfcidoc package (T4.3): pure-Go IDoc parser/builder over
  the EDI_DC40 + EDI_DD40 wire layout. Encode / Decode the
  control record + segment table; suitable for
  IDOC_INBOUND_ASYNCHRONOUS payloads.
- cmd/nwrfc-bridge (T4.4): HTTP/JSON gateway. POST a JSON
  body to /rfc/<FN>; the bridge invokes the RFC and returns
  JSON. Pool-backed; per-error-category HTTP status mapping
  (logon → 401, abap → 400, timeout → 504, comm → 502).
  Designed as a sidecar; does NOT do auth (deploy behind a
  reverse proxy).
- docs/MIGRATION_FROM_GORFC.md (T4.5): mechanical port guide
  from upstream `github.com/sap/gorfc`. Side-by-side examples,
  behavioral-change call-outs (date/time policy, build tag,
  redaction, no-SDK mode, leak fix), Pool/Session/Server
  pointers.

### Stability

- Public API in nwrfc/, nwrfcparam/, nwrfcotel/, nwrfcmock/,
  nwrfcidoc/ is now frozen per docs/PLAN.md §12 decision 12.
  Breaking changes wait for v2.x.

### Out of scope

- 🟡 SAP server callbacks (T3.4 cgo trampoline) ship in a
  point release once a SAP sandbox with bgRFC config
  (SBGRFCCONF) is reachable for validation. The Go-side
  interface (TransactionHandlers / BgRFCHandlers /
  Server.Install*Handlers) is final.

## v0.3.0 — 2026-05-07 (Tier 3: advanced protocols and CLI)

### Added — Tier 3

- tRFC client (T3.1): `Conn.NewTransaction` returns a
  `Transaction` carrying a fresh `TID`. `Transaction.Call` /
  `Submit` / `Confirm` are the lifecycle. The cgo backend's
  Submit/Confirm bindings remain pending validation against
  a SAP sandbox; the Go-side API is final.
- qRFC client (T3.2): `Conn.NewQueuedTransaction(name)`.
  Same shape as tRFC plus a queue name routed via
  `RfcSetQueueName`.
- bgRFC client (T3.3): `Conn.NewUnit(queues...)`. Returns a
  `Unit` with `Call` / `Submit` / `Confirm` / `State`. Uses
  the SDK's `RfcCreate/Invoke/Submit/Confirm/GetState/
  DestroyUnit` family (capability-gated against SDK
  ≥ 7.50 PL5).
- tRFC/qRFC/bgRFC server handler interfaces (T3.4):
  `TransactionHandlers` (OnCheck/Commit/Rollback/Confirm) and
  `BgRFCHandlers` (adds OnGetState). Wired into
  `Server.InstallTransactionHandlers` /
  `InstallBgRFCHandlers`. The cgo trampoline is the
  follow-up; the Go-side API is final.
- Repository abstraction (T3.5): cross-Conn metadata cache.
  `NewRepository().Use(conn).Describe / Preload / Snapshot /
  Apply / Invalidate`. Snapshots are `map[string]
  backend.FunctionDescriptor`, suitable for serializing to
  disk and reloading. Pre-load reduces first-call latency.
- cmd/nwrfc CLI (T3.6): `ping`, `describe`, `call`, `version`
  subcommands. Uses GORFC_TEST_* env vars for connection
  parameters; useful for spot-checking SAP RFC connectivity
  and printing function descriptors as JSON.

## v0.2.0 — 2026-05-07 (Tier 2: observability + providers + sync server)

### Added — Tier 2

- nwrfcparam.BAPIReturn helper (T2.1): typed view of the
  BAPIRET2 ABAP DDIC structure. ParseBAPIReturn handles
  single map / slice / []any shapes the marshaling layer
  emits. AsError converts error-typed rows into
  `*nwrfc.ABAPApplicationError`. CheckRETURN(resp) is the
  one-liner for the conventional RETURN parameter.
- Throughput accumulator (T2.2): `nwrfc.NewThroughput` +
  `Attach(conn)` + `Stats()`. SDK-side counters via
  `RfcSetThroughputOnConnection` (SDK ≥ 7.53 🟡); Go-side
  fallback via Conn lifecycle hooks when SDK is too old.
- nwrfcotel subpackage (T2.3): RedactHandler is a
  slog.Handler wrapper that strips backend.SensitiveKeys
  attributes; recurses into slog.GroupValue. ConnListener +
  TracerListener emit per-event slog records / OTel spans.
  Tracer / Span minimal interface stays version-independent
  of go.opentelemetry.io/otel.
- DestinationProvider + ServerProvider (T2.4):
  control-plane resolution of destination + server
  registrations. SetDestinationProvider /
  SetServerProvider install process-wide resolvers.
  OpenDest now consults provider → IniFS → SDK in order.
- Custom IniFS (T2.5): `IniFS = io/fs.FS`. SetIniFS installs
  a process-wide source. parseIni handles `[DEST=NAME]`
  blocks, comments, KEY=VALUE pairs, with Extra escape
  hatch for unknown keys.
- Metadata cache (T2.6): Conn.Describe goes through the SDK
  cache; InvalidateMetadata wraps RfcRemoveFunctionDesc.
  Repository (T3.5) layers cross-Conn cache on top.
- Synchronous inbound RFC server (T2.7): Server type with
  Register / Start / Stop / Running. SetServerImpl wires
  the cgo backend's RfcRegisterServer +
  RfcInstallGenericServerFunction. Returns
  *UnsupportedFeatureError when no impl is installed
  (no-SDK build).
- Auth-set extensions (T2.8): SSO ticket (MYSAPSSO2),
  X.509, SAML 2.0 / Bearer params surfaced through
  `nwrfc.Params`. Cgo Open path forwards them via the
  generic param map.
- Connection event listeners (T2.9): ConnEvent enum
  (Opened / Closed / Broken) + Listener interface +
  ListenerFunc adapter. Add / Remove / fireEvent
  thread-safe. nwrfc.Open / Close fire automatically.

## v0.1.0 — 2026-05-07 (Tier 0 + Tier 1: production-grade synchronous client)

### Added — Tier 0 (security remediation)

- Removed legacy `gorfc/sapnwrfc.ini` containing real-looking SAP
  credentials and corporate hostnames in `*.wdf.sap.corp`.
- Replaced hardcoded credentials in `gorfc/gorfc_test.go` and
  `example/hello_gorfc.go` with `GORFC_TEST_*` env-var lookups; the
  legacy integration tests are now opt-in.
- New `.gitignore` patterns: `sapnwrfc.ini`, `**/sapnwrfc.ini`,
  `*.pse`, `**/sec/`, `nwrfcsdk/`, `sapcrypto/`.
- New `gorfc/sapnwrfc.ini.example` placeholder profile.
- New `docs/SECURITY.md` v0.
- New `.github/workflows/secret-scan.yml` running gitleaks.
- Tightened `gorfc/gorfc.go` build tag.
- Fixed `defer C.free` capture-before-assignment leak.
- New `docs/FEATURE_MATRIX.md`, `docs/SDK_FUNCTIONS_MAP.md`,
  `docs/ROADMAP.md`.

### Added — Tier 1 (core revival)

- New module path `github.com/cjordaoc/gorfc`. go.mod bumped
  to `go 1.23 + toolchain go1.25.0`. testify v1.10.0.
- New internal/backend, internal/sdkbackend (cgo SAP NWRFC
  SDK), internal/nosdkbackend, internal/ucs2,
  internal/timeext, internal/bcd packages.
- New public nwrfc package: Conn, Pool, Session, Params,
  CallOptions, Call, CallMap, EnsureSDK, SDKVersion,
  Capabilities, the 16-type error hierarchy, the four
  capability-extension wrappers (trace / lang / crypto /
  ini-reload).
- New documentation: docs/INSTALL.md, docs/BUILD.md,
  docs/CONFIGURATION.md, docs/ERRORS.md.

### Changed — breaking from upstream `github.com/sap/gorfc`

- Module path migration.
- Date/time policy: ABAP "00000000"/"000000" no longer
  silently maps to zero `time.Time`.
- Error shape: 16 typed structs + sentinels.

### Fixed

- Memory leak in legacy `fillVariable`.
- Build tag falsely allowed compile on any amd64 GOOS.
- Committed credentials.

### Security

- See docs/SECURITY.md §8 for the historical exposure note.

## Pre-revival (upstream history)

0.2.0 (2020-06-09)
- ABAP datatypes support completed (RFC_DECF16, RFC_DECF34, RFC_UTCLONG).
- Error handling extended with GoRfc error type.
- RFCTYPE_XSTRING wrap fix.
- ABAP input parameters check extended.

0.1.0 (2020-05-04)
- Darwin support.
- New connection parameters added, type changed to map.
- New connection attributes added, type changed to map.
- Table parameter accepts also array of variables.
- ABAP datatypes conversions fixed.
- ABAP INT8 type added.

0.0.1 (2016-02-01)
- Initial release.
